PM SHRI (PM Schools for Rising India) is a Centrally Sponsored Scheme in the state.
Regarding the implementation. The Cabinet of Ministers. Passed on February 14, 2023
A decision was taken in the meeting. PM SHRI (PM Schools for Rising India) is a Centrally Sponsored Scheme.
The scheme has a central and state share ratio of 60:40. for the implementation of the scheme.
The government was considering opening a new head of accounts for Scheduled Tribe applications.
"PM SHRI" is scheduled as per the approval given by the Department of Tribal Development and Department of Finance.
The following new headings are being allowed to be opened for tribal applications:
